<br>
A few weeks ago after I resigned my post in The Black Oath I met Ansur in High Hold Keep.  Between battles we spoke a bit and discovered we had a common interest in trade skills.  We talked a bit more later that night and he told me of his plans for a guild.  Those plans went something like this:  A group of friends, close knit, a bit focus on trade skills and some organized raids/hunts to aquire supplies for trade skills.  I was interested then and I still am.  I have been approached by a couple of guilds and my answer to all of them lately has been, sorry I'm just not looking for anything right now.  And now I have no reason to look, I belive I've found something, or maybe it's found me, but at any rate Ansur, yes I would be pleased to be an officer.<br>
<br>
Sywyn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=braddok>braddok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/23/02 12:53:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=388.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> On the offer to join...</span><hr size=1> I am Braddok, Paladin of Marr and resident of Freeport.<br>
I am honored indeed at the offer to join Ansur's guild.  I am most impressed at how I was recruited.  Ansur uses a lower level character to scout out potential recruits.  I fought alongside him for some time before a guild was ever mentioned.  &quot;Not far...Yoda not far.  Take you to him I will.&quot;  This shows that each member will be very carefully considered and I am honored to know that I made the cut without even knowing I was auditioning.<br>
Ansur's alter-ego fought with valour, camaraderie and a strong sense of right and wrong that helped steer this paladin from making a bad decision.<br>
It is not blustery, roleplaying paladin-talk when I say that this is a guild I will be proud to be a member of.<br>
My thanks,   Braddok <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ansurfv>AnsurFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 119<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/26/02 12:41:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=388.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hello again</span><hr size=1> Well, it has been a rough week trying to recruit. Two of the people who were excited to be forming this guild were wearing the tags of another guild when I saw them today. Where I thought we needed only one more we now need three. <br>
